awd_titl_txt: Mathematical Sciences: Homotopy Theory and Its Applications
awd_abstract_narration: Professor Ravenel wishes to continue his investigation of                  the applications of complex cobordism to homotopy theory.                            Professor Neisendorfer plans to study the product                          decompositions of double loop spaces of Moore spaces and, more                  generally, of the double loop spaces of simply connected finite                 complexes.  He also plans to study the computation of the mod p                 homology of certain function spaces.                                                 Both investigations are efforts to expand the scope of some                standard algebraic techniques for analyzing and classifying high-               dimensional manifolds.  Manifolds themselves are natural                        geometric objects which arise in theoretical physics and                        elsewhere, often as the solution sets of ordinary or differential               equations.
